Dodonaeos : a literary epithet to enhance their value. The caldrons at Dodona (in Albania, about eleven miles to the south-west of Jannina) were suspended 'on oak-trees near a brazen statue which held a lash in its hand. When the wind blew strong the statue was agitated and struck against one os the caldrons which communicatcd the motion to all the rest. From the din so caused the priests drew their predictions.
